What is your project idea (as decided by your team and approved by your teacher)?
Our project idea is a smart water bottle.
This is a water bottle that is smart. It will connect with a smartwatch to track your fitness and tell you when and how much to drink.
Lets you know when you need to drink water(light warning)
Is reusable 
Regulates the temperature of the water
Filters the water 
Leak proof


What kind of website is it (Community, Existing Industry, Startup)?
Startup.


What problem does your project solve?
Solves being dehydrated during workouts or just throughout the day. - Kwesi


Is it a “vitamin” or a “painkiller”? Why?
Vitamin because it is not a necessity but it is nice to have. - Anaishia




How does your project solve the problem?
It solves dehydration of an individual by showing them how much they need to drink in a day, giving them reminders, control the temperature -Julia 


Is your idea similar to another product? If so, how is your idea better/different (what is your “secret sauce” as described in the video)?
The secret sauce is that will track the fitness and is bluetooth connection -Anaishia 


Describe the likely users of your web site.
The likely users of our website will be people who work out often or feel as though they need to drink more water. - Josh


Is the idea simple as described in the How To Choose Business Ideas video?
The idea is simple because there is not much to it and it is easy to understand. - Josh


Is your idea in a growing market or mature market (see video on Growing Markets)?
Its a mature market because water bottles have been around for a very long time - Kwesi


How did you come up with this idea? Describe the process.
We came up with this idea when looking for new innovations to improve daily life. - Josh


What other ideas were candidates?
A smart helmet, a leash for fish -Rocco


Why did you pick this idea over the other candidates?
Because everybody agreed that it was the best idea - Rocco

